Description: Fix CVE-2025-37731 - Extract principal from certificate RDN
 Improper Authentication in Elasticsearch PKI realm can lead to user
 impersonation via specially crafted client certificates. This patch adds
 support for RDN attribute value principal extraction in PKI Realm,
 allowing extracting the principal from a specific RDN attribute (e.g., CN, OU)
 in the client certificate, improving flexibility in identifying users
 based on certificate details.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/commit/cd97b8566bf56e628070021300784cb9cee0286f
Author: Elliot Barlas <elliot.barlas@elastic.co>
Last-Update: 2025-11-20

